LAGOS – No fewer than 150 golfers are anticipated to feature at the 4th Orodje of Okpe Golf Tournament slated for Friday, 4 to Saturday, 5 March 2022 at Sapele Athletic Club Golf Section, Delta State. \Captain of the golf section, Okakuro Gilbert Aghogho stated that the event tagged ‘HRM Orodje 2022’ will feature golfers from various golf clubs across the Southern and Northern part of Nigeria to the ancient city for one of the best-organised golf events in Nigeria. He added: “The tournament is sponsored by Seplat Energy to commemorate the 15th Coronation Anniversary of Orodje of Okpe Kingdom, His Royal Majesty (HRM), Orhue 1 Major General Felix Mujaperuo (rtd), a prolific golfer, and the Grand Patron of the club. “The tournament is a clarion for golfers all over the country to rally round one of their own; Chairman, Traditional Rulers Council of Delta state, The Orodje of Okpe Kingdom. This serves as an invitation to all and sundry of Okpe Kingdom, and golfers all over. “Golfers are arriving from Ibori Golf and Country Club, Asaba; Ogunnu Golf Resort, Warri; Benin Club Golf Section (BCGS); UBTH Golf Club, Benin City. Arsenal Golf Club, Owerri, Imo State; IBB International Golf and Country Club, Abuja; Ikoyi Golf Club, Lagos and many others. “The monarch, being a prolific golfer, his friends and associates will take part in the event whereby winners in men’s and ladies events, veteran and super veteran and other categories will win trophies and many other prizes. “The arrival, registration and cocktail will hold on Friday, March 4, while the ceremonial tee-off and tournament proper holds on Saturday while the presentation of prizes to winners and the dinner party hold in the evening at the section’s pavilion,” said Aghogho.